<Author>Allthingshorsey
<Content>Convenient - value for money We stopped here whilst attending a show at the RAI conference centre. We used the shuttle bus daily to get to and from Schipol where we caught a train to RAI (4 Euro return). Breakfast was included in the price of 69 Euro and was most adequate - Cereals, fruit, meats, cheese, breads, hot scrambled eggs, bacon, sausage, hash browns - more than enough variety.The only reason we'd look for another hotel next time was that the shuttle buses last run from Schipol was at 11:45 which meant leaving the show before it ended - we got a taxi from the RAI one night that was 18 Euro - only 2 of us sharing would have obviouslly been more acceptable splitting it 4 ways.A very pleasant hotel and staff - recommend it. 
