<Author>lolabug
<Content>Very convinient and comfortable hotel! I often stay at this Mercure and think its convinience and affordability make it great hotel for business travellers. The free shuttle from the airport that runs twice an hour is the best feature. You can easily take the shuttle to the airport and then take the train to downtown Amsterdam (or wherever). The rooms are nice and modern with large comfortable beds and nice bathrooms. The room service menu is very limited and I would definitely skip the 17 euro breakfast (it is only cold items!). I recommend getting your breakfast at the airport or at the McDonalds (or even the BP) across the street instead. The grocery store in the arrivals hall at the airport is great for picking up some things to keep in the room.This is a great hotel if you are in town for a quick stay and don't care about being right downtown. They also have special rates for a half day if you have a long layover (cheaper than the hotel in the airport itself). 
